%h1
  %a{:href=>"../"} Bundles >  
  Skysail Server Extension DbViewer

%p
  This server extension provides functionality to manage database connections and to access (view for now)
  the stored data. As usual, as a server extension, it provides a restful interface, communication via JSON.

%h2
  URIs of the Resources

%p 
  Assuming that our application is hosted locally and is listening to port 8554:

%table{:border => 1, :width => "100%"}
  %tr{:style => "background-color:#cccccc"}
    %th{:width => "550"} URI
    %th.edit Description
  %tr 
    %td 
      <b>/dbviewer/connections/</b>
    %td URI of the <font color="red">"connections"</font> resource
  %tr 
    %td <b>/dbviewer/connections/{connectionId}</b>
    %td URI of the <font color="red">"connection"</font> resource where {connectionId} represents the identifier of a connection
  %tr 
    %td <b>/dbviewer/connections/{connectionId}/schemas</b>
    %td URI of the <font color="#0088CC">"schemas"</font> resource
  %tr 
    %td <b>/dbviewer/connections/{connectionId}/schemas/{schema}</b>
    %td URI of the <font color="#0088CC">"schema"</font> resource
  %tr 
    %td <b>/dbviewer/connections/{connectionId}/schemas/{schema}/tables</b>
    %td URI of the <font color="blue">"tables"</font> resource
  %tr 
    %td <b>/dbviewer/connections/{connectionId}/schemas/{schema}/tables/{tablename}</b>
    %td URI of the <font color="orange">"table"</font> resource
  %tr 
    %td <b>/dbviewer/connections/{connectionId}/schemas/{schema}/tables/{tablename}/columns</b>
    %td URI of the <font color="grey">"columns"</font> resource
  %tr 
    %td <b>/dbviewer/connections/{connectionId}/schemas/{schema}/tables/{tablename}/data</b>
    %td URI of the <font color="purple">"data"</font> resource

